name: annual-progress-report-of-the-detroit-river-international-wildlife-refuge-and-the-internat-0dbbd
notes: This annual narrative report for Detroit River International Wildlife Refuge summarizes Refuge activities during the 2010 calendar year. The report begins with a letter from Congressman John Dingell. Followed by an introduction to the Refuge and a summary of habitat conservation efforts.  Information about research and monitoring including insect surveys at Humbub Marsh. Community engagement efforts are discussed along with capacity building efforts. Lastly, upcoming activities and investments are summarized.
